-- BHP: sees 1 million bpd ouput within 5 yrs after Petrohawk deal
-- 
-- Fri Jul 15, 2011 8:00am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/07/15/us-bhp-petrohawk-forecast-idUSTRE76E03X20110715

 

 SYDNEY  (Reuters) - BHP Billiton said on Friday it expects to double oil and oil-equivalent production to 1 million barrels per day within five years, helped by its proposed acquisition of U.S. shale gas group Petrohawk Energy. 

 BHP Billiton currently produces about 500,000 barrels of oil and oil-equivalent per day. BHP Billiton has unveiled a $12.1 billion agreed takeover of Petrohawk. (Reporting by  James Regan ; Editing by  Ed Davies )